                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rather than inventing a new role which may or may not be interesting, make us good at an old role.  In camp crowd control.
<br />

<br />
Let us have the ability to mitigate cutting-edge difficulty NPC dps so that we can survive resists.
<br />

<br />
Change Mind over Matter to a class-defining ability, sort of like Shroud of Stealth or Fading Memories.
<br />

<br />
Change it as follows:
<br />
Duration: 10 hours
<br />
Reuse: Instant
<br />
Hit limit: None
<br />
% damage converted: 50%
<br />
Mana:Hp ratio: 2 mana:1 hp L 1, up to 3 mana:1 hp L 3.
<br />

<br />
This does not make us any better at long term tanking: any creature we can MoM-tank indefinately we can Arcane Rune tank more efficiently.
<br />

<br />
It makes us better at tanking spikes of DPS, like a resisted mez, or a broken charm.  It does this in a way that scales with the DPS of the creature attacking us.
<br />

<br />
This makes mez costs scale with mob difficulty in a very natural way.  It increases our mitigation to tank levels, but costs us mana to maintain it.  It makes our itemization (mana heavy, AC/HP light) work with our main job.  It makes OOW charm less silly (because we can now deal with the broken-charm pet far better).  It makes incamp CC viable, because we can take a resist and live.  It is an ability that is nearly already coded.  It fits with the traditional playstyle of the enchanter, contributing in an area where we don't step on other class's toes.
<br />

<br />
It allows enchanters to compete favourably with offtank strategies on raids (at least until they run oom on resists).  It allows enchanters to compete favourably with out of camp crowd control in xp groups.  XP groups are already capable of single-pulling mobs to camp: the ability to mez and lock down a train isn't as powerful as it was in Kunark, when single pulling was tricky and slow.
<br />

<br />
Our mezzes now balanced based on the kunark assumption, that the ability to mez all but 1 mob is an overpoweringly powerful ability for dungeon crawling (the main source of XP).
<br />

<br />
Our charms are now balanced based on the Tipt/Vxed assumption, of mobs that have low MR, don't summon, are snareable, can equip weapons, and can fully buffed kill a copy of themselves in 10 seconds flat.  And that parties are happy to build groups around controlling the pet and keeping them off the enchanter.
<br />

<br />
Our buffs are now balanced based on the Original era assumption, that enchanter haste and clarity increase a group's DPS by 50% or more, and there are no other viable alternatives.
<br />

<br />
The truth is, parties already single pull.  Mez's quadradic power is long gone.  The truth is, other classes can buff melee and mana regen better than we can (3 for mana, 2 for melee).  The truth is, GoD mobs are not Tipt/Vxed charm bait -- they aren't worth building a group around, and they run faster, have nastier abilities, and are generally more ornery on the "kill the charmer" scale than other expansions.
<br />

<br />
But really, I can live with that.  Just give us back in camp crowd control.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
