                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My proposal in the Brenlo forum:
<br />

<br />
Given the lack of response so far to our requests to adjust the current RvR with charm in OoW zones, I put on my thinking cap to devise a way to make playing my enchanter fun again. My primary concerns were usefulness and fun in groups and raids while keeping myself active (as opposed to just casting debuffs / buffs). 
<br />

<br />
A targeted fade ability would: 
<br />

<br />
1. Enable enchanters to server as pullers in groups where content cannot easily be pacified and/or is hard hitting (Hard LDoN, GoD zones, etc) 
<br />
2. Enable enchanters to survive a mez resist that doesn't one-round them (giving groups amd raids an option to mez instead of single pull or offtank adds) 
<br />
3. Provide enchanters with an active role as agro-reducer on raids (i.e. caster summoned, Fade them) and in groups (tank down, mob goes for healer, Fade them) 
<br />

<br />
For this ability to function without being overpowering, it requires balancing in terms of mana cost and recast. My suggestion is as follows: 
<br />

<br />
1. Make it a spell not an AA (make it use up a spell slot) 
<br />
2. Link the recast timer to all charm spells (to prevent exploits / minimize use for charm soloing) 
<br />
3. Make it a OoW purchaseable / questable spell - level 65 or 66 
<br />
4. Mana Cost 1250 
<br />
5. Recast 60 seconds 
<br />
6. Limit the /target ability to group only, same as invisibility 
<br />

<br />
With that mana cost, enchanters cannot use it casually. Recast of 60 seconds is fast enough to permit an enchanter to function as a puller (something many of us did in LDoN), but slow enough to prevent serious exploits.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Nokei Orhaste</a></span>
<br />
Coercer for <span style="color: blue"><a href="http://www.houseofaegis.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">House of Aegis</a></span>
<br />
Luclin
<br />
&lt;Retiring 11/02/04&gt;
<br />

<br />
E66.191/L h++ 2.8khp 4.6km ft12 BK10
<br />

<br />
It`s never fun until the druid dies.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
