                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">CC imbalance was caused by the fix made to pacification and then the proliferation of pacification like abilities to puller classes.  Enc are not a primary puller class because we lack one thing: the ability to totally remove agro in a short amount of time.  CC in camp versus pulling singles has been an ongoing deterioration of our core class ability since FD was discovered to be a great pulling mechanism (this was not originally intended in the "vision").  Since this has become the preferred method for crowd control, we rarely see much action here.
<br />

<br />
Charm imbalance was more recent as a result of the game progressing to a point where gear (and to a lesser degree AA) provided such a distinct advantage over mobs of the same level that their DPS and HP were increased to keep up with the player's gear.  At 69, my HP is just over 1120 without gear.  With gear, I'm over 5 times that number.  
<br />

<br />
Regardless of how people see enchanters today, these two abilities defined our class 5 years ago.  We get mez at level 4 and charm at level 12.  We used to not even see mana regen until level 29.  This is how many of us grew in the game.  And people who chose not to use both of these two functions are really missing out on what it means to be an enchanter.
<br />

<br />
All of our other abilities allow us to make a choice on what to put in our spell gems to help deal with the game environment when we are limited or reduced in functionality for our two core abilities.
<br />

<br />
Fade may be a great utility, and it might be a welcome addition to the enchanters.  It is, in essence, a form of memblur.  I'm not sure I see the difference, however, between Fade and our current memblurs other than the recast and cast time.  But I'm still waiting for something to change for the better so we bring back our core abilities -- not something that in essence forces us to compete with classes who are already strong in pulling.
<br />

<br />
Frankly, I am not interested in becoming a primary pulling class.  I'm not interested in being a nuking class.   I'm not interested in being a buff bot.  I didn't start my enc nor do I continue to play my enc for any of those roles.  I'm now out there looking for a replacement to EQ; I'm hoping  for WoW and EQ2 to be better than the current EQ market so I can switch to one of them.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=406237" target="_blank" class="postlink">Baalazai</a>
<br />
Rodcet Nife
<br />
<a href="http://www.echoesineternity.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Echoes in Eternity</a>
<br />

