                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Monks are in enough trouble already, lets not try to take their role. I want to be good CC again, even in high zones. I want it to be faster and more efficient to bring 2-3 mobs than to bring 1, like it used to be. In KT, MPG, RS, etc, that is just not the case, since mobs resist mez so much, and when they do, half the time we are a bloody spot on the floor, and group dies afterwards. That makes it far better to bring singles than multiples. 
<br />

<br />
If our mez is supposed to be nothing but a panic button, at least make it one that works, and lower the resist rate (ie, up the resist adjust on our mezzes). 
<br />
If our mez is supposed to be an active tool, make us able to survive a mez resist, or we won't be allowed to use that tool by our group mates.
<br />

<br />
The combination of high resist rates and almost zero defense is what makes today's mezzing so out of whack.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2212" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.elerion.net/pics/sjhosig.jpg" border="0" /></a><span style="font-style: italic"><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">
<br />
"Carrot Cake Soup is like the taste of watching girls make out. It has an extraordinary power that oscillates between gentle and overwhelming, between light and dark, between pleasure and more pleasure." - Penny Arcade</span></span></center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
